  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Global Health Research Group on Early Childhood Development for Peacebuilding</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To create a sustainable network of early childhood development (ECD) researchers and practitioners from six countries affected by conflict. 2) To share knowledge and expertise across participants of the network and build research capacity in country to support the development and robust evaluation of ECD programmes. 3) To build specialist research capacity at Centre for Evidence and Social Innovation (CESI) to undertake global health research in relation to ECD,through the support of Yale and NYU. 4) To support the evaluation of ECD pilot programmes in six LMIC partner count ries that are to be delivered through support from UNICEF. 5) Work with UNICEF and the wider global Early Childhood Peace Consortium (ECPC) to develop and implement effective advocacy strategies for ECD programmes within partner countries and internationally. 6) Develop and implement a strategy to generate external funding to sustain and grow the network beyond the current three-year funding window in alignment with ECPC.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A UK and low- and middle-income country (LMIC) partnership that aims to support the implementation and  evaluation of early childhood development programmes and the potential to promote sustainable development and peacebuilding in LMICs affected by conflict.</narrative>
  </description>
